	<div id="review_process"><h2>Our Review Process</h2></div>       
	<h3>Step 1: Content Analysis</h3>
	<p>The perfect resume tells a story. It takes the reader through a consistent and positive recap of the candidate's career history. We aim to provide detailed revisions that will help you achieve this story across all areas of your resume.
	</p> 
	<ul>
		<li>We evaluate the words and statements provided in all sections of your resume.</li>
		<li>After reviewing the content, we assess the general theme and message you are portraying as the candidate and optimize for that throughout the resume.</li>
		<li>Once we have a clear understanding of your experience, education, and goals we decipher and analyze each sentence throughout the resume.</li>
		<li>For certain sentences we will provide commentary and analysis, while for others we will offer written alternatives for your use.</li>
		<li>Our goal is to tell a consistent positive story, using well-written sentences and very specific detail that will make you stand out to the reader.</li>
	</ul>
	<h3>Step 2: Grammar Review</h3>
	<p>A poorly written resume with grammatical errors is an easy criteria to filter out unwanted resumes. After all of the hard work adding great content to your resume, don't fall victim to something as trivial as grammatical errors.
	</p> 
	<ul>
		<li>After thoroughly reviewing, editing, and commenting on the content throughout your resume, the next step in our process is to re-read all sections to assure all grammar is correct.</li>
		<li>This includes, but is not limited to reviewing the use of periods, capitalization, tenses, action-verbs, and repetitiveness.</li>
	</ul>
	<h3>Step 3: Format Review</h3>
	<p>We don't believe in a one-size-fits-all layout. To us the key is to make sure that your resume catches the reader's eye and when we review your format we look for consistency, uniqueness, and professionalism - all of the key elements to make sure you don't get lost in the pile.
	</p> 
	<ul>
		<li>The last and final step in our review process is to evaluate the overall format of your resume.</li>
		<li>We look for consistency, uniqueness, and professionalism when formatting a resume.</li>
		<li>We will tweak the formatting of your current resume, or often provide an entire reformat to display alternatives to your current style.</li>
		<li>Our goal is to make sure that your resume stands out in the most positive way possible, and to eliminate any chances for it to be overlooked because of poor formatting.</li>
	</ul>
